        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Euro falls relative to dollar, to 84.12 cents; graph; exchange rates for other currencies listed (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>EURO FALLS. The euro fell against the dollar as doubts mounted that the European Central Bank would buy the currency for a second time to stem its decline. In New York, the euro dropped to 84.12 cents, from 84.37.</p>
      </block>
